The Met today refused to name the man.

It came as a different pensioner, who was earlier arrested in south London as part of the Jimmy Savile sex probe, has been released without charge.

The 65-year-old was held in February on suspicion of sexual offences and taken into police custody.

But a spokesman for the Metropolitan Police said today there was insufficient evidence to prosecute.

The freed man was also arrested in the 'others' strand.

Most of the allegations relating to 'others' have been made against people associated with the entertainment industry, including ex-glam rocker Gary Glitter and comedian Freddie Starr.

PR guru Max Clifford, TV star and comedian Jim Davidson and entertainer Rolf Harris are also among those who have been arrested.

