So far, 589 people have come forward with information relating to the scandal, with 450 alleging they were sexually abused by former Top Of The Pops presenter Savile.

Of those making complaints about the late DJ, 73 per cent were children at the time of the offences.

A report released in January revealed that Savile's victims included an eight-year-old boy and children who were seriously ill.

Branded one of the UK's most prolific known sexual predators, Savile now has 214 criminal offences recorded against his name, including 34 rapes.

